race.comment: MERIDIANA (4) top class mare who had a chequered run with the 59.5kg when a desperately unlucky second over 1500m at Randwick in the Four Pillars. Key jockey change and looking for this trip and further now. Ticks plenty of boxes. FEAR NO EVIL (5) smart gelding who will take catching second-up after proving too classy on resumption when scoring over 1300m at Bendigo. Goes just as well second-up and can go on with it this prep. ROTAGILLA (8) bounced off his unlucky first-up fourth with a dominant victory over 1500m at Randwick. Jumps quickly in weight and sure to be thereabouts. ECLAIR ENCORE (10) talented mare who looks set for a big campaign judging by her two eye catching runs over the shorter trips. Gets weight relief in this stronger contest and stalks the good pace. Value chance. RAPBIDASH (13) at her top now and gives the indication she's looking for this trip. Will be surging late.
